SIMPLE: insinuative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insinuative
<hw>In*sin"u*a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>insinuatif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Stealing on or into the confidence or affections;
having power to gain favor.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Crafty, <xex>insinuative</xex>,
plausible men.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Reynolds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Using insinuations; giving hints; insinuating;
<as>as, <ex>insinuative</ex> remark</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insinuator</ent>⟦br⟧
